**WARN: (TCLCMD-1557):	The 'set_clock_sense' command has been replaced by the 'set_sense' command in SDC2.1 specifications.'set_clock_sense' command still works but it is recommended to switch set_sense as per SDC 2.1 guidelines.

Usage: set_clock_sense [-help] <pin_or_port_list> [-clocks <clock_list>] {-positive | -negative | -stop_propagation | -logical_stop_propagation | -stop <type_list>}

-help                         # Prints out the command usage
<pin_or_port_list>            # List or collection of pins or ports
                              # (string, required)
-clocks <clock_list>          # List of clocks passing through the specified
                              # objects to which the constraint applies
                              # (string, optional)
-logical_stop_propagation     # Stops the propagation of specified clocks
                              # passing through the specified objects
                              # (bool, optional)
-negative                     # Positive phase filtered clocks pass through the
                              # specified objects (bool, optional)
-positive                     # Negative phase filtered clocks pass through the
                              # specified objects (bool, optional)
-stop <type_list>             # Applies clock sense to object types specified
                              # in type_list: {all clock data clock_source_data
                              # default_data} (string, optional)
-stop_propagation             # Stops the propagation of specified clocks and
                              # clock source data paths passing through the
                              # specified objects (bool, optional)